estinal haemorrhage. Postoperative pain scores (at rest or with movement). Any indicator for postoperative bowel motility: incidence of ileus, time to first bowel sounds, flatus, bowel movement, or time to first drinking or eating. Any indicator for postoperative mobilization: any type of functionality score or time to first ambulation. Length of intensive care unit (ICU) stay. Length of hospital stay.", "rejection_reasons": "", "other_info": "This review compares different analgesia methods and assesses various outcomes in abdominal aortic surgery."}
