d significantly lower pain scores, especially on postoperative day 1.\n\n**Summary:**\nPain assessment using a verbal/visual analog scale showed that intervention groups experienced less pain compared to control groups, particularly on the first postoperative day.\n\n### Final Analysis\nThe appendices provide comprehensive data on postoperative complications, extubation criteria, and pain assessment. The consistent definitions of complications suggest standardized outcomes for clinical assessment. Extubation management varies by study protocol, indicating differences in surgical practices. Pain assessment highlights the effectiveness of interventions in reducing postoperative discomfort.\n\nIf you need further analysis or specific details from these appendices, feel free to ask!"}
